data.text: @SilenceInSparta I have 0 faith that these men are acting in any motivation but to increase their own personal well-being with no consideration of others.
@wickhelm Why wouldn't they want 12% of the country (or more) lifted to greater wealth so they can sell more products? Seems logical to believe the wealthy want strong economies and trade
@SilenceInSparta Lemme put my faith in two rich dudes. Lmao ok

@wickhelm If you believe that sincerely then you're admitting you don't have the power to change these things. Maybe the President and the biggest celebrity in America can do it together. Im rooting for those things to change and i hope they succeed.
@SilenceInSparta Nothing is going to change. People are still going to get their right to vote removed, poverty will continue to get worse, and racism will continue to impact the lives of thousands.

@wickhelm Republicans are being kinder to Kanye than Kap bc Kanye is starting a dialogue with them. Kap is calling them evil and Ye says lets fix these problems together. Which one do you think gets more accomplished?
